<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-418-531  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 418 531.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  July 12 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Australia: tax dept opens modernisation info section.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>McNamara, Sean.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Australia. Taxation OfficeAustraliaTax LawSupport ServicesGovernment AgencyInformation Services.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>AUSTRALIA: TAX DEPT OPENS MODERNISATION INFO SECTION MELBOURNE, AUSTRALIA,1990 JUL 9 (NB) -- The Australian Taxation Office [ATO] has opened itsInfoPlace section where members of staff and the public can receiveinformation about the ATO's modernisation program.andM;The section will incorporate a help desk, computer training, software supportfor new and existing systems, and an information service for staff to informthem of changes due to the AUS$700M modernisation program.andP;  Databasedevelopment training courses are already under way in the section, with theaim of having staff experienced in database development by the end of theyear.andP;  Quarterly reviews of InfoPlace's activities will be conducted toensure the office is meeting the needs of its users.andM;(Sean McNamara/19900711)</TEXT></DOC>